In the Philoctetes of Sophocles the appearance of Heracles ex machina is needful in order that the struggle between two human wills‚ neither of which could yield without an inconsistency fatal to the dramatic picture, might be terminated by an expression of the divine will. In some at least of the plays of Euripides there is also ‘dignus vindice nodus', an entanglement that calls for a deliverer.
